###
# Azure AI Translator - Text Translation REST API Examples
# 
# This file contains comprehensive examples of using Azure AI Translator service
# to translate text, detect languages, and handle various scenarios.
#
# Prerequisites:
# 1. Azure subscription with Translator resource
# 2. Set the following variables in your environment or replace directly:
#    - {{TRANSLATOR_KEY}}: Your Translator resource key
#    - {{TRANSLATOR_ENDPOINT}}: Your Translator resource endpoint
#    - {{TRANSLATOR_REGION}}: Your Translator resource region
#
# Usage:
# - VS Code with REST Client extension
# - Replace variables with actual values
# - Click "Send Request" above each request

### Variables (replace with your actual values)
@translatorKey = {{TRANSLATOR_KEY}}
@translatorEndpoint = {{TRANSLATOR_ENDPOINT}}
@translatorRegion = {{TRANSLATOR_REGION}}

###
# 1. Basic Text Translation - Single Language
# Translate "Hello, how are you?" to Spanish
POST {{translatorEndpoint}}/translate?api-version=3.0&to=es
Content-Type: application/json
Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key: {{translatorKey}}
Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Region: {{translatorRegion}}
X-ClientTraceId: {{$guid}}

[
    {
        "text": "Hello, how are you?"
    }
]

